@oxtopus - please review

fixes #631 

Update setup.py link flags, reuse third party FindCapnProto.cmake script, clean up environment variables. The main purpose of this is to allow users to have capnproto preinstalled and have everything work the same as the source install. The `SOURCE_CAPNP` option allows users to force a source build.

Removes docextract/refextract/authorextract.

Depends on bibedit and bibcatalog removal due to imports from those modules. Also some useful functions where moved into classifier module which uses them.

@jirikuncar @jmartinm

## Summary

Excludes contenttypes app from the fixtures. I had to manually delete them, but it was an easy fix in this case. In the future use the `--exclude=contenttypes` option for `dumpdata` @66eli77.

@jamalex if you rebase after this is merged, you should be able to run tests.

Allows us to wait until an action has actually been completed before
returning a result.

@tvansteenburgh @johnsca I'm not sure whether this is the right approach. Should we push responsibility to manage the observer to the code making the call? Or should we generalize some of the techniques here, and push them further into the codebase? (Also, it's intuitive to me to return stdout, stderr, and code for what is essentially a remote bash command, but I'm open to changing what we return.)

- {% extends "base.html" %} -> {% extends "oscar/base.html" %}
- {% extends "layout.html" %} -> {% extends "oscar/layout.html" %}

This allows having independent base.html and layout.html in template root.

Other templates remain untouched, and e.g. creating template dashboard/layout.html will still override oscar/dashboard/layout.html. This might still cause problems if the project has another app named dashboard, for example.

Fixes #1378

Current view (current backend doesnt return nested todo list):
<img width="1365" alt="screen shot 2018-06-18 at 5 50 50 pm" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3481095/41564398-a7eea276-7320-11e8-90c6-c26fdfc7b505.png">

Once the backend starts returning nested todo list, the tree view will look like following:
<img width="317" alt="screen shot 2018-06-18 at 5 36 53 pm" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3481095/41564409-b167fdf2-7320-11e8-8284-15a9fe1569ed.png">

Here is the response format required by the tree view template:
```
[{
        'id': 1,
        'description': 'THINGS NOT TO DO',
        'completed': false,
        'items': [
          {
            'id': 11,
            'description': 'node1.1',
            'completed': false,
            'items': [
              {
                'id': 111,
                'description': 'node1.1.1',
                'completed': false,
                'items': []
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            'id': 12,
            'description': 'node1.2',
            'completed': false,
            'items': []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        'id': 2,
        'description': 'GETTING STARTED',
        'completed': false,
        'items': [
          {
            'id': 21,
            'description': 'node2.1',
            'completed': false,
            'items': []
          },
          {
            'id': 22,
            'description': 'node2.2',
            'completed': false,
            'items': []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        'id': 3,
        'description': 'ADD/UPDATE CONTENT',
        'completed': false,
        'items': [
          {
            'id': 31,
            'description': 'node3.1',
            'completed': false,
            'items': []
          }
        ]
      }]
```

